### Problem Description

geo_point runtime fields are returning values as "lat,lon" strings  instead of GeoJSON. 

### Steps to Reproduce

Run the commands below in Kibana console. Notice the response how `test_location` is returned as `"-37.91000002529472, 144.6599999908358"` instead of GeoJSON


Create index
```
PUT test
{}

PUT test/_doc/1
{}
```

Request
```
GET test/_search
{
  "_source": false,
  "fields": [
    "test_location"
  ],
  "runtime_mappings": {
    "test_location": {
      "type": "geo_point",
      "script": {
        "source": "emit(-37.91,144.66)"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Response
```
{
  "took" : 0,
  "timed_out" : false,
  "_shards" : {
    "total" : 1,
    "successful" : 1,
    "skipped" : 0,
    "failed" : 0
  },
  "hits" : {
    "total" : {
      "value" : 1,
      "relation" : "eq"
    },
    "max_score" : 1.0,
    "hits" : [
      {
        "_index" : "test",
        "_id" : "1",
        "_score" : 1.0,
        "fields" : {
          "test_location" : [
            "-37.91000002529472, 144.6599999908358"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

